roll`\n- `LaunchedEffect` changed to `scrollState.animateScrollTo(scrollState.maxValue)`\n- Messages changed from `items(messages)` to `messages.forEach`\n- Result: Build SUCCESS, installed. But gap still visible because `Column(weight(1f))` still fills all space.\n\n#### Attempt 2: PersonalizationConfigCard collapsed by default\n- Changed `var isExpanded by remember { mutableStateOf(!isConversationStarted) }` to `var isExpanded by remember { mutableStateOf(false) }`\n- Also attempted `Arrangement.Bottom` on scrollable Column — this caused \"huge space ABOVE header\" (user complained)\n\n#### Attempt 3: Arrangement.Bottom (FAILED)\n- Added `verticalArrangement = Arrangement.Bottom` on outer scrollable Column\n- User reported: \"теперь огромное пространство над заголовком и при открытии клавиатуры аналогичная проблема\"\n- Reverted\n\n#### Attempt 4: Conditional LazyColumn weight + Spacer\n- Changed to: when no messages, `LazyColumn` has no weight (wraps content); when messages exist, `LazyColumn(weight(1f))`\n- Added `Spacer(weight(1f))` between LazyColumn and input when empty\n- Result: Functionally same as before - same gap (Spacer fills it instead of LazyColumn)\n\n#### Current State (partial fix in progress)\n- Reverted back to `LazyColumn(weight(1f))` always (the stable working approach)\n- `PersonalizationConfigCard` stays collapsed by default (done)\n- The LazyColumn conditional modifier revert in progress when context ended\n\nCurrent state of `ChatScreen.kt` at time of context compaction - the last edit was reverting the conditional modifier back to always `weight(1f)`:\n```kotlin\nLazyColumn(\n    modifier = Modifier.weight(1f).fillMaxWidth(),\n    state = listState,\n```\n\nThe `Spacer` for empty state was still present and needs to be removed.\n\n### Key files modified in this session:\n1. `.env` (created)\n2. `local.properties` (created)\n3. `.gitignore` (updated)\n4. `desktop-app/build.gradle.kts` (BuildConfig field)\n5. `androidMain/EnvLoader.kt` (rea